In this statement, the President acknowledges the celebration of Diwali by Hindus, Jains, Sikhs, and some Buddhists. He describes Diwali as a time for gathering with loved ones, enjoying good food and dancing, and also for prayer and reflection on the less fortunate. The President praises the compassion of these communities in helping those affected by Hurricane Sandy. He mentions the lighting of the Diya lamp, symbolizing the triumph of light over darkness and knowledge over ignorance. The President also refers to the shooting at a Sikh gurdwara earlier in the year, highlighting the community's resilience and the support they received from people across the country. He concludes by wishing those celebrating Diwali a happy celebration.